程序包 P2V

类 SubViewer

java.lang.Object
P2V.VObj
P2V.SubViewer
public class SubViewer extends VObj
SubViewer is a class that represents PGraphics class in the P2DViewer. It extends the VObj abstract class and inherits its properties and methods. However, it also can render VObjs just like P2DViewer class. Using SubViewer might cause performance problems.
作者:
Telsa

    • putVObjToTopByIndex

      public void putVObjToTopByIndex(int index)
      Move the VObj with the specified index to the end of the objs list. Attention, SubViewer renders graphics in the order specified by the objs list, so the graphics that are placed towards the end of the list will be less likely to be obscured. This is also why the function "putVObjToTopByIndex()" actually puts the VObj object at the end of the objs list.
      参数:
      index - The ID of the VObj to remove.

    • putVObjToTopById

This is also why the function "putVObjToTopByIndex()" actually puts the VObj object at the end of the objs list.
      参数:

      返回:

    • drawObj

      public void drawObj() throws Exception
      Draws the objects contained in the SubViewer. This method is responsible for rendering the objects within the SubViewer onto the associated PGraphics instance. This method calls the actualMove() method of each object to update its movement. If you add SubViewer into P2DViewer, when you call P2DViewer.drawObj(), this method will be automatically called too.
      抛出:
      Exception - if an exception occurs during the rendering process.
